summary:
A psychology graduate, a curious human and a life enthusiast. I’m passionate about learning about people and their cultures, and figuring out how our lives can be improved. An eager advocate for equity, diversity, and inclusion. 

I have experience with qualitative and quantitative research, and particularly enjoy data analysis in R. I’m interested in organizations that bring positive value to the world, making it a better place to live for all.  Currently working as a Junior Researcher at IEA, joining them on their mission to improve education worldwide.
